  "commentary": "With SPX at 6572.3 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6550 and max positive gamma at 6600, dealers are currently in a buy-the-dip mode having just crossed above the 6550 amplifying zone where they were forced to sell into weakness. The breakout regime with -13.9B total GEX means dealers will continue amplifying moves - they'll aggressively buy any dip back toward 6550 and sell rallies into the 6600 resistance wall where +8.9B in positive gamma creates a natural ceiling. Watch 6550 as the critical support (dealers become buyers below) and 6600 as the key resistance (dealers become sellers above) - a clean break of either level should see accelerated moves due to the amplifying nature of negative gamma positioning.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550 and 6600 with potential for explosive moves if either level breaks.",
